Air France Luggage Policy:

Carry-On Luggage:
Passengers are allowed to bring one carry-on bag and one personal item such as a purse or laptop bag.
The maximum dimensions for the carry-on bag are 55cm x 35cm x 25cm (21.7in x 13.8in x 9.9in) including handles, pockets, and wheels.
The maximum weight allowed for the carry-on bag is 12 kg (26 lbs).
Passengers traveling in La Première and Business are allowed to bring two carry-on bags, each weighing a maximum of 18 kg (39.7 lbs).

Checked Luggage:
The checked baggage allowance depends on the class of service and the destination.
For Economy Class, the allowance is up to 1 piece of luggage, up to 23 kg (50.7 lbs) for most destinations and 2 pieces of luggage, up to 23 kg for destinations in the Americas, India, and Israel.
For Premium Economy and Premium Economy Class, the allowance is up to 2 pieces of luggage, up to 23 kg each.
For Business and La Première, the allowance is up to 2 pieces of luggage, up to 32 kg (70.5 lbs) each.
For all classes, the maximum dimensions for each checked bag are 158 cm (62in) (length + width + height).

Excess Baggage Fees:
If passengers exceed their luggage allowance, excess baggage fees will apply. The fees vary by destination and can be paid online or at the airport.
It

s checked baggage policy varies based on the route, fare class, and frequent flyer status of the passenger. Here is a breakdown of the policy:

For flights within Metropolitan France:
- Economy Light: No checked baggage allowance
- Economy Standard: 1 bag up to 23kg
- Flight with Plus passage: 1 bag up to 32kg
- Business: 2 bags up to 32kg each

For flights within Europe:
- Economy Light: No checked baggage allowance
- Economy Standard: 1 bag up to 23kg
- Flight with Plus passage: 1 bag up to 32kg
- Business: 2 bags up to 32kg each

For flights between Metropolitan France and North America, Central America, and the Caribbean:
- Economy Light: No checked baggage allowance
- Economy Standard: 1 bag up to 23kg
- Premium Economy: 2 bags up to 23kg each
- Business: 2 bags up to 32kg each
- Flying Blue Silver, Gold, and Platinum members: 1 extra bag up to 23kg

For flights between Metropolitan France and South America:
- Economy Light: No checked baggage allowance
- Economy Standard: 1 bag up to 23kg
- Premium Economy: 2 bags up to 23kg each
- Business: 2 bags up to 32kg each
- Flying Blue Silver, Gold, and Platinum members: 1 extra bag up to 23kg

For flights between Metropolitan France and Africa, Middle East, Asia, and Oceania:
- Economy Light: No checked baggage allowance
- Economy Standard: 1 bag up to 23kg
- Premium Economy: 2 bags up to 23kg each
- Business: 2 bags up to 32kg each
- Flying Blue Silver, Gold, and Platinum members: 1 extra bag up to 23kg

Additional baggage can be purchased at varying rates depending on the route and fare class. Oversized and overweight baggage may also incur additional fees. Passengers are recommended to check Air France

s overweight baggage policy varies depending on the route and fare type. 

For long-haul flights to/from the Americas and worldwide, overweight baggage is categorized as any item weighing between 51 lbs and 70 lbs (23 kg and 32 kg). Extra fees apply and vary based on the origin/destination and fare class. 

For example:

- An overweight bag from Europe to the Americas or Caribbean in Economy Light will cost $100, while in Economy Standard it will cost $200.
- On a flight from Asia to Europe, Economy tickets will incur a fee of $25 per kg over 23 kg and Premium Economy/Business/First tickets will pay a fee of $125 per kg over 23 kg.

If an item weighs more than 70 lbs (32 kg), it cannot be transported as standard baggage and must be shipped as cargo. 

It

s policy for oversized baggage is determined by the weight and the size of the item. Any item that exceeds the maximum weight and size limits is considered oversized baggage. Here are the oversize baggage rates for travel with Air France:

- For flights within Metropolitan France and to Europe, the following fees apply:

     - Checked oversized baggage between 23kg and 32kg -€150/$175
     - Checked oversized baggage between 32kg and 45kg - Not allowed
     
- For intercontinental flights and flights to the French Overseas Departments and Territories, the following fees apply:

     - Checked oversized baggage between 23kg and 32kg - €300/$350
     - Checked oversized baggage between 32kg and 45kg - €600/$700
     
- If the oversized baggage weighs more than 45kg, it cannot be transported on Air France flights. 

Air France oversize baggage maximum dimensions: 

The maximum dimensions for checked oversized baggage allowed on Air France flights are:

- Length + width + height = 203cm/ 80in 
- No dimension can exceed 158cm/ 62in 

If the size and weight of oversized baggage exceed the maximum limits, additional fees will be charged, or the item may be refused. Air France suggests checking with the airline beforehand to avoid any surprises and to ensure the safe transportation of your items.

The pet policy for Air France states that cats, dogs, and birds are allowed to travel in the cabin or the hold, provided that they meet certain requirements. 

In the cabin: 
- Only cats and dogs weighing no more than 8 kg (including their carrier) are allowed. 
- A maximum of 1 pet per passenger is permitted. 
- Pets must be enclosed in a carrier that fits under the seat in front of the passenger. 
- The carrier dimensions must not exceed 46 cm x 28 cm x 24 cm. 

In the hold: 
- Cats, dogs, and birds can be transported in the hold. 
- The pet and carrier must weigh less than 75 kg. 
- Advance reservation is mandatory. 
- The carrier must be of an approved type and meet the IATA (International Air Transport Association) standards. 
- Water and food must not be provided in the carrier. 

Additionally: 
- Certain breeds of dog are prohibited from transport by Air France. 
- Pets must have the necessary documents for travel, such as a health certificate and proof of vaccination. 
- There is an additional fee for bringing pets on board, which may vary depending on the destination. 

Please note that these regulations are subject to change at any time and it is always advisable to consult with Air France directly before traveling with your pet.

Air France offers complimentary meals and beverages on all of its intercontinental flights. The in-flight dining experience is designed by Michelin-starred chefs and features a range of options to accommodate various dietary restrictions and preferences. Passengers can also pre-order special meals such as vegetarian, gluten-free, or Kosher meals at least 48 hours before their flight departure.

On short and medium-haul flights, complimentary snacks and drinks are offered on most flights. However, on select routes and in their premium cabin, Air France offers a wide selection of hot meals and beverages.

Passengers can also purchase additional snacks and beverages on board depending on the duration of the flight. Furthermore, Air France offers a variety of alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverages, including beer, wine, spirits, coffee, and soft drinks.

For passengers traveling in its La Première cabin, Air France offers a dining experience featuring dishes prepared by renowned chefs. This includes a personalized menu, a champagne bar, and an a la carte menu.

In addition to the traditional in-flight meal service, Air France also offers a range of snacks, sandwiches, and beverages in its lounges. The airline also has partnerships with various gourmet food and beverage brands to offer exclusive products to its passengers.

s flight change policy allows passengers to modify their itinerary within certain conditions. The conditions vary depending on the ticket fare class and destination. The airline"s standard change fee ranges from €70 to €150 per person per one-way flight. Additionally, if the new flight has a higher fare than the original flight, the passenger must pay the fare difference.

Passengers who purchased a Flex or Pro fare can change their flight without a change fee. However, a fare difference may still apply if the new flight has a higher fare than the original flight. Passengers who purchased a basic economy fare (Light) are not allowed to change their flight.

Passengers may change their flight up to 2 hours before the scheduled departure time. If the change is made less than 48 hours before the scheduled departure time, the airline recommends that passengers contact the Air France customer service center to avoid any issues.

Air France also offers a

option, which allows passengers to modify their itinerary free of charge up to 24 hours before the scheduled departure time. This option is available for purchase during the booking process. However, if the passenger decides to cancel the flight, the airline will not refund the cost of the Flex option.

Passengers can make changes to their itinerary online via the Air France website, mobile app, or by contacting the airline"s customer service center. Changes made online may be subject to a lower change fee than those made through the customer service center.

In the event of a flight cancellation or schedule change by the airline, passengers are entitled to a full refund or a new flight at no extra charge. Air France will notify passengers of any changes via email or text message.

Air France Cancellation Policy

Air France allows passengers to cancel their flight ticket under certain conditions. Passengers must cancel their flight ticket at least 24 hours before the scheduled departure time to avoid cancellation charges. 

If a passenger cancels their flight ticket within 24 hours of booking, they are eligible for a full refund without any cancellation charges. Passengers who had booked a non-refundable ticket will be charged a cancellation fee if they cancel their flight ticket after the 24-hour grace period. 

Air France charges a cancellation fee ranging from 45 Euros to 200 Euros, based on the fare type, destination, and route. The cancellation fee may also vary based on the departure date, time, and the number of remaining days before departure. 

Passengers may cancel their flight ticket online through the Air France website or mobile app, by calling the Air France customer service center, or by visiting the Air France ticket office. Refunds will be credited to the original form of payment within a few business days. 

In some cases, Air France may also allow passengers to change their flight ticket instead of canceling it. Passengers must check their fare type and the terms and conditions before requesting a change. Additional fees may apply for changing the flight ticket.

Travel Insurance Policy for Air France

1. Coverage: The travel insurance policy offered by Air France covers trip cancellations, trip interruptions, trip delays, and baggage delays. It also includes emergency medical and dental coverage, emergency medical transportation, and accidental death and dismemberment coverage.

2. Trip Cancellations and Interruptions: If your trip is canceled or interrupted due to a covered reason, such as illness, injury, or death of a travelling companion or family member, you will be reimbursed for any non-refundable expenses you have incurred.

3. Trip Delays: If your trip is delayed by a covered reason, such as a natural disaster or severe weather, you will be reimbursed for any additional expenses you incur, such as hotel accommodations or meals.

4. Baggage Delays: If your baggage is delayed by a covered reason, such as a flight delay or lost luggage, you will be reimbursed for the purchase of essential items, such as clothing and toiletries, up to a pre-determined amount.

5. Emergency Medical and Dental Coverage: If you become sick or injured while travelling, the travel insurance policy will cover the cost of emergency medical and dental treatments, up to a pre-determined maximum limit.

6. Emergency Medical Transportation: If you require emergency medical transportation, such as air ambulance or medical repatriation, the travel insurance policy will cover the cost of transportation up to a pre-determined maximum limit.

7. Accidental Death and Dismemberment Coverage: If you suffer accidental death or dismemberment during your trip, the travel insurance policy will provide coverage up to a pre-determined maximum limit.

8. Exclusions: The travel insurance policy does not cover pre-existing medical conditions, illegal activities, or acts of war or terrorism.

Note: This is only a summary of the travel insurance policy offered by Air France. Please refer to the policy documents for the complete terms and conditions of coverage.

Overweight Baggage Policy for Alaska Airlines:

1. For domestic flights, overweight bags weighing between 51-100 pounds will be charged an additional fee of $100 per bag.
2. Overweight bags weighing over 100 pounds will not be accepted for travel.
3. For international flights, overweight bags weighing between 51-70 pounds will be charged an additional fee of $100 per bag.
4. Overweight bags weighing over 70 pounds will not be accepted for travel.
5. Oversized bags that exceed the standard size and weight limitations will be charged an additional fee, regardless of the weight of the bag.
6. Alaska Airlines reserves the right to adjust overweight baggage fees based on individual circumstances.

Cabin pet policy:
- Alaska Airlines allows one pet per guest in the cabin.
- The pet must be able to fit comfortably in an approved carrier that slides under the seat in front of you.
- The maximum carrier dimensions are 17

high for Boeing aircraft.
- The combined weight of the pet and carrier cannot exceed 20 pounds.
- The pet must remain in the carrier and under the seat for the duration of the flight.
- The fee for bringing a pet in the cabin is $100 one-way.

Cargo pet policy:
- Alaska Airlines accepts pets for transport in the cargo hold on certain flights.
- All pets traveling in the cargo hold must have a health certificate issued within 10 days of travel.
- The combined weight of the pet and carrier cannot exceed 150 pounds.
- The pet must be at least 8 weeks old and fully weaned.
- The fee for transporting a pet in the cargo hold varies depending on the route and size of the pet"s carrier. Please check with Alaska Airlines for specific pricing.
- Alaska Airlines offers a Live Animal Service Guarantee for pets traveling in the cargo hold, which provides compensation in the event of an accident or delay.

- Alaska Airlines offers a wide variety of food and beverage options for purchase on our flights, ranging from snacks and light meals to full entrees and alcoholic beverages.
- In First Class, we offer complimentary meals and beverages, including wine and beer.
- In Main Cabin, passengers can purchase snack boxes, sandwiches, salads, and other food options.
- Alaska Airlines also offers special meals for passengers with certain dietary restrictions, such as vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, and kosher meals. These meals must be requested at least 24 hours in advance of the flight.
- We recommend passengers bring their own food and non-alcoholic beverages if they have specific dietary needs or preferences.
- Outside food and beverages are not allowed on Alaska Airlines flights, except for baby food and breast milk/formula.
- In accordance with federal regulations, Alaska Airlines does not serve alcohol to passengers under the age of 21.
- Alaska Airlines reserves the right to limit or prohibit alcohol sales to any passenger who appears to be intoxicated or disruptive.

Special Meal Policy for Alaska Airlines:

1. Passengers with dietary restrictions or food allergies can request special meals during their travel with Alaska Airlines.

2. The airline offers a range of special meals including vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, kosher, and Halal meals.

3. Passengers can request their special meals online during the booking process or by contacting the Alaska Airlines reservations team at least 24 hours prior to their scheduled flight.

4. Passengers should carry their own medication and/or food supplements as Alaska Airlines does not provide these items on board.

5. Passengers are advised to check the specific meal options available on their flight prior to making a request.

6. Passengers can modify or cancel their special meal request up to 24 hours before their scheduled flight.

7. Alaska Airlines does not guarantee the availability of special meals on all flights and routes.

8. In case the passenger does not receive their requested special meal, Alaska Airlines will provide an alternate meal option that is closest to the passenger

s seat location and fare type.

- Carry-on baggage:
Passengers are allowed to bring one carry-on bag and one personal item onboard. The carry-on bag must not exceed 22 x 14 x 9 inches (56 x 36 x 23 cm), including handles and wheels, and must fit in the overhead bin. The personal item must be able to fit under the seat in front of the passenger and can include a purse, briefcase, or laptop bag.

- Checked baggage:
The number of checked bags allowed varies based on the ticket type, destination, and loyalty status. The weight and size limits for checked bags also vary depending on these factors. For most destinations, the standard weight limit for each checked bag is 50 pounds (23 kg), and the maximum overall dimensions for each bag are 62 inches (158 cm). Fees may apply for certain destinations or excess weight.

- Special items:
Special items such as sports equipment, musical instruments, and fragile or perishable items may require additional fees and restrictions. American Airlines recommends contacting their reservations or special assistance department ahead of time to confirm the guidelines for traveling with special items.

- Prohibited items:
Certain items are not allowed to be carried onboard or in checked baggage, including explosives, firearms, and certain chemicals and gases. For a complete list of prohibited items, passengers should check with American Airlines or the Transportation Security Administration (TSA) website.

- Lost or damaged baggage:
If luggage is lost or damaged during the flight, passengers should report it to American Airlines customer service or baggage service office at the airport as soon as possible. American Airlines has policies in place for compensating passengers for lost or damaged baggage, subject to certain limitations and conditions.

American Airlines allows passengers to bring one personal item and one carry-on bag on board. The personal item must fit under the seat in front of you, while the carry-on bag must fit in the overhead bin or under the seat in front of you. 

The maximum size for the personal item is 18 x 14 x 8 inches (45 x 35 x 20 cm) and must be able to fit completely under the seat in front of you. Acceptable examples include a purse, briefcase, or laptop bag. 

The maximum size for the carry-on bag is 22 x 14 x 9 inches (56 x 36 x 23 cm), including any wheels and handles. The bag must fit completely in the overhead bin, or under the seat in front of you if the overhead bin is full. 

American Airlines also has weight restrictions for both items. The personal item cannot weigh more than 18 pounds (8 kg), while the carry-on bag cannot weigh more than 22 pounds (10 kg). 

Additionally, passengers traveling with infants are allowed to bring a diaper bag on board in addition to their personal item and carry-on bag. The diaper bag must also fit under the seat in front of you and can have a maximum size of 18 x 14 x 8 inches (45 x 35 x 20 cm). 

Certain items such as strollers, walkers, and some medical equipment may be considered as assistive devices and not counted towards the carry-on allowance. 

Passengers who violate the carry-on policy may be required to check their bag at the gate and pay applicable baggage fees.

Travel Insurance Policy:

American Airlines offers a travel protection plan that provides coverage for trip cancellation/interruption, emergency medical expenses, baggage loss/delay, and travel accident insurance.

Benefits:

- Trip Cancellation/Interruption: Reimbursement of non-refundable trip costs if the trip is cancelled or interrupted due to covered reasons such as illness, injury, death, and other unforeseen events.
- Emergency Medical Expenses: Coverage for necessary medical expenses due to sickness or injury that occur on the trip.
- Baggage Loss/Delay: Reimbursement for the cost of necessary items if baggage is lost or delayed for a certain amount of time during the trip.
- Travel Accident Insurance: Accidental death & dismemberment coverage during the trip.

Terms & Conditions:

- Must purchase travel insurance within a certain timeframe after making initial trip payment.
- Pre-existing medical conditions may not be covered.
- Must provide proper documentation and follow claim procedures for reimbursement.
- Coverage limits and exclusions may apply.

Cost:

The cost of travel insurance varies based on the trip cost and the level of coverage selected. Prices start at $25 per person for basic coverage and can go up to $2,000 for premium coverage.

Note: This information is a brief summary of the American Airlines travel protection plan. Please refer to the full policy details and terms and conditions for complete information.
